title: For Sale/Trade:  Stainless INOX Beretta 92fs w/ stainless controls 9mm
postcontent:
I have a really nice all stainless beretta 92fs . "All stainless" refers to the controls on the gun also being stainless ( ie mag release, slide release, takedown lever,safety,hammer,trigger) .Beretta forum members spend $200 in parts alone to make theirs all stainless and this one came this way from the factory . A few other things make this 92fs highly collectible . The first is that it has the straight dustcover like the m9 ,all newer 92fs models are slanted dustcover which doesn't look as nice and these are hard to find in black much less stainless. The second thing is that it has the radius cut backstrap(allows for better purchase or grip on the pistol and shorter reach to trigger )which is rarely seen combined with the straight dustcover and also in stainless. Gun comes with nice wooden grips w/beretta medallions($60 grips), two brand new 17rd  factory mags(new production flush fit) , case and is in excellent condition. Factory black grips in 3rd pic are also included. Gun was made in 1999 and it appears to have been shot a few times and put away for years. You don't see them like this often. One thing I forgot to mention is that this even has a stainless locking block and stainless guide rod(new models have plastic guide rods)These new sell for around $700 with the cheap black plastic controls and slanted dustcover so I am asking $725 but will entertain reasonable offers. I know what these sell for on auction websites so please dont throw out silly offers.These dont come up for sale very often. No low ballers, must sign bill of sale and have valid VA ID.  

Note: The second picture shows the dustcover differences, if you notice the slanted dustcover model has the radius cut backstrap which is the common model, usually the straight dustcover isnt paired with the radius backstrap but it is the holy grail of the 92fs in my opinion as its the best of both worlds, better looking and better feel in the hand.

title: For Trade:  M1 Garand for your Ruger Super RedHawk Alaskan .454
postcontent:
Only Looking to trade my M1 Garand for a Ruger RedHawk Alaskan 2' in .454/.45lc.
Not looking for the .44 mag version but thank you.


It will come with a genuine Korean war Web sling, and 50 rounds or .30/06, and about 50 empty re-loadable brass.

Up for grabs is my "made in America" M1 Garand!

My serial number was produced in April 1939. Overwhelming odds are that this rifle saw active duty in WWII due to the high demand in those early years. Think about it... my serial number is 10**0 and troops were not fully issued until serial number 400,000+


Here is the reason it is stamped CAI:


1. America left a lot of firearms in foreign countries after WWII.

2. The gun control act of 1968 gave the ATF power to regulate imports.

3. ATF then started requiring all firearms entering America to be stamped by the importer. This included American arms "returning' to our country.

4. So the serial number and "CAI" stamp simply means that the rifle left the country prior to 1968 and returned after that. A virtual guarantee that it saw active duty in at least one and possibly several wars.

Hello everyone from ghost munitions I'd like to introduce our latest product to the ghost munitions line of brass and cleaning solutions. 

We are now manufacturing rotary tumblers for home reloaders and commercial companies alike. Here are the specs for our offerings 

We start out with an all steel frame welded together by hand right here in America. marathon county WI to be exact utilizing the best and as many made in America products as we can we assemble our tumblers in house. 

What about capacity? 

This is where YOU the customer has to do a little leg work.  We want to provide the most efficient tumblers we can not only with low energy motors and water sensible cleaning but we want to provide a product that fits you. Normally we use a tank constructed by hand from American made pvc. For our commercial guys these tanks are 8" in diameter and approximately 22" long giving you the flexibly to run 500 pcs of 9mm to 1500 cases of 5.56 brass. If you are just a hobbyist we also have you in mind we can customize a tank that best fits you for both production and space. These are not made in China machines that will break after a week and anyone that's used or seen a cement mixer for using stainless steel media knows they are loud and inefficient.  

We can make tanks from 6" x 10" to 8"x24" one thing to consider is weight. Utilizing about 4 gallons of water and approximately 30 pounds of pellet pins a full large tank can be as much at 80# not a problem for some but not everyone needs that kind of capacity. 

So what all do I get? 

Tumblers will ship fully assembled ready to use. All you'll need to do is fill your tank with brass and media a little dawn some lemi shine top it off with warm tap water and away you go. 

What about shipping? 

These bad boys are not light weighting in at approximately 75# or a hair over we would like to ship these as best we can for the most cost effective rates if you are located in Wi we would be more than happy to have you by the shop to pick yours up or we can deliver for fuel cost. Nationwide we will acquire a shipping quote before an order is finalized. 

How about price? 

Pricing is going to be $450 for our large tumbler and smaller tumblers will be slightly less. All tumblers are custom built by hand so no worries about "out of stock on that model but we have this one right here for a little more." That's not how we believe customers should be treated.

title: For Sale:  Ghost munitions: rotary tumblers
postcontent:
Hello everyone from ghost munitions I'd like to introduce our latest product to the ghost munitions line of brass and cleaning solutions. 

We are now manufacturing rotary tumblers for home reloaders and commercial companies alike. Here are the specs for our offerings 

We start out with an all steel frame welded together by hand right here in America. marathon county WI to be exact utilizing the best and as many made in America products as we can we assemble our tumblers in house. 

What about capacity? 

This is where YOU the customer has to do a little leg work.  We want to provide the most efficient tumblers we can not only with low energy motors and water sensible cleaning but we want to provide a product that fits you. Normally we use a tank constructed by hand from American made pvc. For our commercial guys these tanks are 8" in diameter and approximately 22" long giving you the flexibly to run 500 pcs of 9mm to 1500 cases of 5.56 brass. If you are just a hobbyist we also have you in mind we can customize a tank that best fits you for both production and space. These are not made in China machines that will break after a week and anyone that's used or seen a cement mixer for using stainless steel media knows they are loud and inefficient.  

We can make tanks from 6" x 10" to 8"x24" one thing to consider is weight. Utilizing about 4 gallons of water and approximately 30 pounds of pellet pins a full large tank can be as much at 80# not a problem for some but not everyone needs that kind of capacity. 

So what all do I get? 

Tumblers will ship fully assembled ready to use. All you'll need to do is fill your tank with brass and media a little dawn some lemi shine top it off with warm tap water and away you go. 

What about shipping? 

These bad boys are not light weighting in at approximately 75# or a hair over we would like to ship these as best we can for the most cost effective rates if you are located in Wi we would be more than happy to have you by the shop to pick yours up or we can deliver for fuel cost. Nationwide we will acquire a shipping quote before an order is finalized. 

How about price? 

Pricing is going to be $450 for our large tumbler and smaller tumblers will be slightly less. All tumblers are custom built by hand so no worries about "out of stock on that model but we have this one right here for a little more." That's not how we believe customers should be treated. 

If interested we would love to hear from you. 

We accept money orders, checks, PayPal and major credit cards processed via intuit go payments. 

Stand by for pictures coming soon 

Thanks and keep your head down. Ghost Munitions team
